Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:19.91,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't supposed to be \Nlike this, head in my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:26.25,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Struggling to escape from \Nthis saturated world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:32.01,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes like whispering sand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:35.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,These circumstances, unchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:38.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,gazing out at a dreamless tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.64,0:00:45.81,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna say goodbye to the \Nconfusion of yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.19,0:00:51.23,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,I try reaching out, as if to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:56.95,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,We cry millions of times \Nand then get born again
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:01:00.16,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go with these red eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:03.37,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,to that pictured future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:08.96,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Come here right by me, \NI'm clapping my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:11.05,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.05,0:01:15.42,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Strain my eyes in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.42,0:01:21.06,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Can't see anything, don't know \Nanything, but I'll still go
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.31,0:01:27.39,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,To the place of shining \Nlight in which you wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.98,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Six
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.98,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,The Code Too Simple
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.98,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by Ango Sakaguchi’s "Angou"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.15,0:01:35.24,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}East Kanto Social Rehabilitation Promotion Center
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.98,0:01:35.74,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,The Social Rehabilitation \NPromotion Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.94,0:01:39.28,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It's one of the prisons built through \Nthat private sector initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.82,0:01:43.37,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I was just one of many first-time \Noffenders confined here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.62,0:01:47.16,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,My speech during the \Nwar ran afoul of the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:50.33,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,New Information Privacy \Nand Protection Act,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.33,0:01:52.63,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,so I was imprisoned \Nthere 'til last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.46,0:01:57.13,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, Mr. Yajima, you \Nwere Kaishou Rinroku's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.17,0:01:58.55,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.17,0:01:58.55,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.97,0:02:01.18,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,We were friends during \Nour university days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:02.30,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yajima
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:02.30,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Critic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.30,0:02:06.60,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I studied literary criticism, \Nwhile his field was technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.60,0:02:08.69,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, you're relying on Shinjurou?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:10.94,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,A trap? Could this be a trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.56,0:02:12.40,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inga
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.56,0:02:12.40,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Detective's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.94,0:02:12.86,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I can't ask Kaishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:17.70,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, it has to be you \Ntwo, who stand against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:22.74,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Yajima...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.24,0:02:25.49,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.25,0:02:28.83,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would be able to \Nmake your acquaintance here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.42,0:02:31.00,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you have a stomach illness or...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:32.38,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.09,0:02:35.55,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that, my release \Ndate has been moved up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:37.38,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like you to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:40.09,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,It's from my personal belongings, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.63,0:02:42.76,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you don't see this book every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.76,0:02:44.81,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I have a copy of it myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.22,0:02:48.43,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.43,0:02:54.06,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.06,0:02:52.02,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Kaishou Rinroku's...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:54.06,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Most definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.57,0:02:55.98,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you get this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.98,0:02:58.99,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,A secondhand bookstore before \Nthey put me in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:01.57,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,May I keep it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:04.83,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see the look of surprise on \NKaishou's face when I give it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:07.91,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It won't do much for his \Nreputation if it gets out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:10.00,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,that books from his own private \Nlibrary are on the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:12.54,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,By all means.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.54,0:03:13.50,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:14.71,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be going then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.13,0:03:19.01,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're here, too, I surmise \Nthat you're also not well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.47,0:03:20.88,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:31.89,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,This, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:33.73,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.19,0:03:38.03,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And that man dropped this slip of paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.03,0:03:38.98,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:42.32,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It probably fell out from \Nbetween the pages of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.32,0:03:43.78,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:49.33,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It's printed on my own \Npersonalized manuscript paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.83,0:03:52.00,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,This is my manuscript paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.29,0:03:55.25,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Then did you write this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:56.75,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:04:00.88,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, this book is \Nfrom Kaishou Rinroku's collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.38,0:04:04.30,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Why was a piece of my manuscript \Npaper between its pages?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:08.47,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You called on me to solve that mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:11.60,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,How could it have gotten in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.60,0:04:12.81,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:15.48,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know the whole story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:18.23,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you just ask Mr. Kaishou?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.23,0:04:20.53,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he would \Ngive me a straight answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.07,0:04:22.44,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.11,0:04:25.36,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't I check it for fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:27.57,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who is this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:28.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can{\i0} you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:30.54,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,If you have some electronic \Ndevice, I can manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.33,0:04:33.50,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,You have a cell phone, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:35.83,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sasa Kazamori
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:35.83,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Artificial Intelligence (R.A.I.)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.17,0:04:39.63,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I'm getting it. I'm getting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:40.96,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:42.59,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.77,0:04:53.48,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,She's not human?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.48,0:04:54.89,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,She's human.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.89,0:04:56.27,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,She's a RAI.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.27,0:04:56.85,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,RAI?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.85,0:05:02.07,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Metro Police Dept.\N Fingerprint Database
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:04:59.40,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,They're banned, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.61,0:05:07.70,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,I've detected two sets of prints that \Nare registered in the MPD database.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.28,0:05:10.20,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,One belongs to you, Mr. Yajima.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:11.83,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,The other...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.83,0:05:12.95,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:15.25,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Yajima Takako.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.25,0:05:16.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Yajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.75,0:05:17.79,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,My wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:22.46,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It makes sense that your wife would \Ntouch your manuscript paper, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:25.13,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... True.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.89,0:05:30.14,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}You broke it! You broke it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:31.76,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Breaking through security \Noverloaded the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:32.39,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Kazamori broke it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.39,0:05:36.02,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shinjurou! Kazamori broke it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:41.90,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So Yajima Takako's fingerprints are in \Nthe Metro Police Department's database...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.90,0:05:43.28,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.61,0:05:45.11,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,This could be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:48.91,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If it leads to catching Kaishou out...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:53.54,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Can I eat Kaishou's soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:58.96,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,"34-14-14"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.67,0:06:01.34,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Could this refer to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:06.72,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,...the 14th character in \Nthe 14th column on page 34?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.01,0:06:11.18,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, the \Nfirst character is {\i1}i{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.18,0:06:14.22,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,The next one is... {\i1}tsu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:16.39,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,And then... {\i1}mo{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.39,0:06:19.06,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,See?! It's becoming a sentence!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:21.40,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, the next letter is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:26.74,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,({\i1}Itsumo no tokoro ni imasu{\i0}...?)\N"I'll be at the usual place"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.74,0:06:30.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I'd save you some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:32.66,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:34.58,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,If you deciphered it yourself, \Nyou should've said so right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:37.41,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't even call it a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.71,0:06:39.71,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It was far too simple and basic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:44.75,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But if the paper and the book were \Nseparated, no one would be able to crack it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:47.38,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,True... So?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.38,0:06:50.22,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Why was this paper in my father's book?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:52.14,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's what {\i1}I{\i0} wanna know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:54.56,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll be at the usual place"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.85,0:06:57.06,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Kaishou Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.85,0:06:57.06,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Daughter of Kaishou Rinroku,\NLives at Home
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:06:56.93,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,A message about a rendezvous?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:59.60,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,But for something like that, they just \Ncould've gone with a text or phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.14,0:07:03.31,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the person was someone who \Ncouldn't be met if it left a record...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:05.86,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to say that it's someone \Nwith a criminal connection or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.86,0:07:06.69,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:11.24,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I believe your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:13.53,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,She passed away when I was three.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.53,0:07:15.03,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,But what does that have to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:16.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.12,0:07:18.08,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:21.46,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, where's \Nthat Inga woman right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.46,0:07:22.54,Main Dialog,Waitress,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:24.54,Main Dialog,Waitress,0000,0000,0000,,Here are your crepes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.46,0:07:28.13,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take a bite then \Ntell me it's not sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:31.13,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,It's a crepe, all right, \Nbut it's {\i1}real{\i0} food.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:34.26,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I invited you to lunch because I \Nfigured you don't eat decent meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:38.06,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Parts of Southeast Asia were \Ncolonized by the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.68,0:07:40.43,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I've had them any number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:49.44,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,A secondhand bookstore?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:51.15,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.15,0:07:52.91,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I have that book right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.32,0:07:54.66,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.66,0:07:56.45,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where was that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:07:58.74,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,This book?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.74,0:08:00.62,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:05.17,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.04,0:08:05.17,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,It looks the same, but it's counterfeit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.17,0:08:06.59,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:10.80,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Kaishou Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:10.80,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Chairman of JJ Systems
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:10.80,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Family Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:10.80,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Head Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:09.05,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,If it's billed as being from \NKaishou Rinroku's library,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:10.59,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,the price of the book would go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.09,0:08:13.43,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't put it up \Nfor auction, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:24.65,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,But let me take a look at the fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:28.19,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Rie...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.36,0:08:33.28,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,"The usual place"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.74,0:08:37.53,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yajima... Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:41.25,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, you went out several times \Non errands for Father, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.25,0:08:45.21,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say you were going \Nto Mr. Yajima's house then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:49.92,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, as his friend \Nwas in prison then,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:52.30,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,he had me go to the house to deliver \Ntoys to Mr. Yajima's children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:55.34,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Were just his wife and children there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:08:55.80,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:08:58.26,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Is his wife pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.64,0:09:05.52,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right. Never mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.98,0:09:11.07,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku says it's not his book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:13.82,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, as a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.70,0:09:16.82,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It seems very fishy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:18.70,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Fishy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.12,0:09:22.54,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If a book that you have no recollection \Nof selling finds its way to the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.54,0:09:24.41,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,you would naturally \Nsuspect thievery first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:27.79,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But apparently, he didn't \Nlook worried at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:29.88,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:31.92,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yajima...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.42,0:09:36.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,When you got the book, you \Nbroke the code too, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:39.68,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll be at the usual place"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.68,0:09:42.22,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was a note \Nsummoning Kaishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.22,0:09:44.85,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,And from a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.19,0:09:51.36,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Under the guise of borrowing the \Nbook, the code was concealed within.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.02,0:09:56.49,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that two people \Nexchanged the same book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:10:00.78,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this very copy was \Noriginally the one in my own home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:04.87,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Then the person who wrote the \Ncode on your manuscript paper...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.67,0:10:08.50,Main Dialog,Takako,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:10.63,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yajima Takako
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:10.63,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yajima's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.25,0:10:10.63,Main Dialog,Takako,0000,0000,0000,,Is someone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.34,0:10:12.88,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.88,0:10:15.51,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,How many times have I \Ntold you that I'm home?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:16.26,Main Dialog,Takako,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.63,0:10:17.38,Main Dialog,Takako,0000,0000,0000,,Darling...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:21.60,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in the middle of \Nwork, so get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.47,0:10:25.10,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful on your way back...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.81,0:10:28.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,How long has your wife been blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:31.94,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It happened while I was in \Nthe correctional center.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.90,0:10:35.19,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,After our children went missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:37.11,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Your children...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:39.32,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Kidnapping was suspected...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.91,0:10:42.62,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,...but my wife ran around \Nlooking for them herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:44.54,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, there were apparently
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:47.04,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,even anti-government terrorist \Nattacks around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:51.92,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,When my wife returned home,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.92,0:10:55.38,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,she was blind and her memories \Nof the time are foggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.96,0:10:58.17,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,After that, my wife called \Nover a used book dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:11:01.18,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,and sold off almost all of my books.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:06.02,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,And you can see what she did to all the \Ndrawings that our children had made.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.60,0:11:09.52,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,As if she wanted to forget everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:13.52,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,This volume may be one of \Nthe books that she sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.06,0:11:16.57,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And what about your children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.57,0:11:19.11,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,They were never found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:21.74,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost been a year now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.33,0:11:27.62,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,When you sleep with a woman, which \Nside of the bed do you sleep on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.83,0:11:31.79,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Do you sleep with that RAI?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.67,0:11:39.30,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Takako always snuggled up \Nto me on my right side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:41.47,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,For all the years we've been together...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.05,0:11:44.09,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I'm left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:49.27,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,But after coming back, Takako sleeps \Non the left side, on the right side...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:53.23,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was due to her blindness \Nat first, but then I realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:57.15,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku is right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:02.78,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.11,0:12:06.53,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Kazamori said she wanted \Nto see the camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.53,0:12:07.33,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:11.58,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't throw me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:13.08,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the RAI from the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:14.00,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:16.71,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,I hacked into the footage \Nof a surveillance camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:19.71,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,At least six times in the past year,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:23.47,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou's car was parked \Nin front of this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.14,0:12:26.10,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.35,0:12:27.47,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:32.14,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Even if my wife did have that kind \Nof relationship with Kaishou,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:33.35,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I can't blame her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.10,0:12:39.98,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,As a result of sticking to my \Nconviction, I was in prison for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:41.99,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,But my children...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:43.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:46.28,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,If Takako did anything to the children
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:49.33,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,because they were in the way of \Nher relationship with Rinroku...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:52.37,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find out where your children are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:54.42,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's your real request, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.58,0:13:00.21,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,No... You've already done what I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:05.84,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I think the souls in this \Nhouse are about to burst!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:08.97,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask that woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.81,0:13:11.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What do you wanna ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:12.68,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:15.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"Where are your children?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.85,0:13:19.27,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You think that mother killed them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:22.90,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Kaishou helped her...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:27.66,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,If that's how it is, all of the truths \Nand lies he's been saving up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.66,0:13:30.16,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,His soul will be laid bare!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:32.49,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.49,0:13:33.50,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Get away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.70,0:13:34.62,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:37.21,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,A colored pencil. It's an instrument \Nused to draw pictures on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:38.00,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.46,0:13:40.50,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,A drawing?! I'm gonna \Ndraw! I'm gonna draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.50,0:13:42.09,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What should I draw on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:42.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh. What is he, a little kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:43.34,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}A sheet of construction \Npaper or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:44.97,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Construction paper? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:51.01,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Kazamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.43,0:13:53.89,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What was used to write on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.89,0:13:54.77,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:55.56,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Just answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.56,0:13:58.10,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, you're a slave driver...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.73,0:14:03.28,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,Pigment and wax...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.53,0:14:06.45,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,The ingredients for a \Ntypical colored pencil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.41,0:14:10.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What's the nearest used \Nbookstore from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.12,0:14:12.16,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a GPS!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.16,0:14:13.37,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.37,0:14:14.70,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori S,0000,0000,0000,,Roger...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:25.13,Main Dialog,Shopkeeper B,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.60,0:14:35.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All{\i0} of the books in Mr. Yajima's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.35,0:14:37.77,Main Dialog,Shopkeeper C,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We took them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.77,0:14:41.40,Main Dialog,Shopkeeper C,0000,0000,0000,,They were all fine volumes, so the \Nwhole bunch soon sold off at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:42.31,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Who bought them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.82,0:14:44.23,Main Dialog,Shopkeeper C,0000,0000,0000,,That's personal information!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.23,0:14:45.65,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I really need to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.65,0:14:49.32,Main Dialog,Shopkeeper C,0000,0000,0000,,No can do! If I told you \Nthat, I could get arrested!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:54.37,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for my \Nfather, he isn't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:56.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.54,0:14:57.87,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to ask a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.37,0:15:02.17,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop, Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:04.13,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be scolded for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:05.25,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:08.55,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,What... on earth... \Nare you looking for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.55,0:15:09.34,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Used books!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:13.10,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, Kaishou bought a collection \Nof books from a secondhand store.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:16.93,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,They were all originally sold \Nfrom Mr. Yajima's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:18.85,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, they're not over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:21.15,Main Dialog,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.44,0:15:25.52,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are these all books, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:29.82,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,More?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:36.74,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Shinjurou, is there something \Nbetween my father and Mr. Yajima's wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.74,0:15:38.29,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we break the code together?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.29,0:15:44.84,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got the courage, the answer \Nto your question is probably in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.35,0:16:00.02,Main Dialog,Takako,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:06.65,Main Dialog,Takako,0000,0000,0000,,Akio... Kazuko...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:12.53,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to say \Nanything, Takako...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:14.07,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hear it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.71,0:16:30.76,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.09,0:16:39.97,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll be waiting at the \Npool. July 10th, 3pm..."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.97,0:16:44.06,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"I have sweets. Keep \Nit a secret from Mom."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.06,0:16:46.36,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,"Don't worry about Mom."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:51.99,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's play at the usual \Nplace. July 12th, 11am."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.99,0:16:55.11,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Akio! Kazuko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.12,0:16:59.99,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The children were using books from your \Nlibrary to play with coded messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:03.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is they did it so \Nas not to worry their mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.04,0:17:05.08,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,who had been acting strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.29,0:17:08.63,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Then, where are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:12.59,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that is also in the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.38,0:17:18.39,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,This is a new play area \Nthat Kazuko found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:20.22,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,Here...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:25.64,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to say this, but there have \Napparently been several incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.89,0:17:27.65,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,of children being trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:32.90,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.07,0:17:37.82,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much time \Nit takes, I'll find them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:40.28,Main Dialog,Yajima,0000,0000,0000,,I've already kept them \Nwaiting for a year...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:56.68,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,You've been spending a lot \Nof time with my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:17:58.51,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kaishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.51,0:18:05.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make several visits \Nto Mr. Yajima's house
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:08.35,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,because his wife was acting peculiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.06,0:18:10.27,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Neglect...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:14.07,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,There were signs of child neglect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.19,0:18:16.74,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Koyama Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.19,0:18:16.74,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Public Prosecutor\N Joint Coordinating Dept.\N Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:17.15,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,She paid no attention to the children,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:19.82,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,so the son had to take care of \Nhimself and his younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:21.53,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,She was lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:26.58,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Takako really loves Yajima,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.54,0:18:30.04,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,so when the children disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.04,0:18:33.42,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,she realized for the first \Ntime just what she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:36.34,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,And she blamed herself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:43.72,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,When we got the report \Nfrom Chairman Kaishou,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.72,0:18:46.02,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I moved to keep it from \Nturning into an incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:50.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So you covered up the child abuse and \Nas a result, the children's lives were...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.90,0:18:54.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same thing as \Ncovering up your own crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.69,0:18:58.61,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,After you've been in love a few times,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.61,0:19:01.16,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,at best you realize \Nhow trivial it all is,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:03.95,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,but even that doesn't \Nmake you any smarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.95,0:19:08.87,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, despite that, without \Nlove, life cannot exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.34,0:19:14.92,Main Dialog,Kazuko,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.80,0:19:20.13,Main Dialog,Akio,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.97,0:19:22.14,Main Dialog,Akio,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:26.72,Main Dialog,Akio,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:31.23,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Once I saw the slips of paper inside \Nthe books that Takako sold off,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:33.19,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I broke the code right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:34.77,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Since it was so simple...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.07,0:19:39.86,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,And then I found the children, \Nburied under a fallen car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:43.45,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Their lives weren't in danger,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.78,0:19:45.16,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Hayami Seigen
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.78,0:19:45.16,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Director of the Security Bureau \NMetropolitan Police Dept.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.45,0:19:45.62,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,but after considering Mrs. \NYajima's state of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.62,0:19:48.20,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I had them placed in \Na child-care facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.75,0:19:50.29,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.58,0:19:54.67,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you reveal the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:57.09,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,For the souls...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.72,0:20:04.60,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Is there always one truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.35,0:20:07.06,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yajima Kazuko
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.35,0:20:07.06,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yajima Akio
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.35,0:20:07.06,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Yajima's Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.35,0:20:07.06,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yajima's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.93,0:20:07.06,Main Dialog,Kazuko,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.98,0:20:14.19,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,You exceeded my expectations...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.11,0:20:17.82,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one who stamped this \Nbook with Kaishou's ownership mark
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:20.44,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,before giving it to Mr. Yajima?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:22.82,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,There's no fooling the \NDefeated Detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.16,0:20:27.33,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe I'd better call \Nyou the "Great Detective".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:29.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.87,0:20:31.75,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:33.37,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,A novelist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.08,0:20:35.92,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I write novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.54,0:20:39.30,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Calls Himself a Novelist
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.54,0:20:39.30,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Prisoner
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.25,0:20:39.76,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Not with a pen, but in reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:41.88,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the Great Detective's deductions,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.88,0:20:43.59,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,all of the mysteries were to be revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.88,0:20:46.89,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,and Yajima was supposed \Nto kill his own wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.06,0:20:50.14,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And what did you try to set that up for?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.14,0:20:53.44,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's the role \Nof the Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.14,0:20:56.73,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how cruel the \Nend result will be,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.73,0:20:59.23,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,after all of the victims \Nhave been murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.23,0:21:01.24,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,the Great Detective wraps everything \Nup with his brilliant deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.90,0:21:06.03,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how tragic the reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.03,0:21:09.12,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,the Great Detective exposes \Nit all to the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:14.08,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,You were {\i1}chosen{\i0} by me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.37,0:21:17.25,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,...to be this world's \Nlast great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.60,0:21:36.15,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,In the pale morning \Nmist, a whispered prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:44.15,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna follow this \Ntwisted landscape with you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.61,0:21:52.16,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the "truth", \N"a 'lie' will do" is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.49,0:22:00.54,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing it as if we can see through
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.54,0:22:04.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, beyond words
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:08.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a falling feather
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:11.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.39,0:22:16.89,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.20,0:22:36.33,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, unravel it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.33,0:22:40.46,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a tattered cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.46,0:22:43.30,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.17,0:22:48.51,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.39,0:22:52.05,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode is inspired from...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.05,0:22:56.06,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Not "Meiji-era Ango Detective Stories" \Nor even a mystery story at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:22:57.43,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"The Retard"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:00.27,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. But I figured we \Nwere gonna do this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.27,0:23:01.69,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better take this \Nopportunity to do it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.69,0:23:04.57,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,since it's not a word you can \Nreally say on TV these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:05.53,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,"Retard", "retard"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.53,0:23:07.32,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't dub in like "idiot".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:10.36,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, it's not a mysterioso \Nthing, but a war story.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.36,0:23:11.91,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,How is this gonna be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:14.16,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on UN-GO: "Daydream".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:14.16,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 7
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:14.16,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,"Daydream"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:14.16,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by Ango Sakaguchi's\NMeijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Detective Stories)\N"Foolish Apparition" and "The Retard"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.16,0:23:15.74,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! I'm not in the next episode?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.74,0:23:17.41,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What's the deal with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.41,0:23:20.08,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I wanna talk to someone in charge!
